  "text": "The possibility of collecting cotton stalks and using them for energy production was investigated by Gemtos and Tsiricoglou [CITATION_1] . It is proved that the feasibility of harvesting cotton stalks using conventional machinery giving the possibility to collect energy material with a total energy content of 500,000 tons of oil equivalent at national level. A generalized pyrolysis model for the oxidative pyrolysis of wood was investigated by Lautenberger and Fernandez-Pello [CITATION_2] . It was found that the specific heat capacity for wet wood, dry wood and char falls between literature values for generic wood and specific data for white pine.",
